# WalkWars — User Stories

**Version:** 1.0  
**Format:** Epic → User Story → Acceptance Criteria

Priority: **P0** = Phase 1 MVP, **P1** = Phase 1 nice-to-have, **P2** = Phase 2

---

## Epic 1: Authentication

### US-1.1 Register account (P0)

**As a** new user  
**I want to** create an account with username, email, and password  
**So that** I can track walks and compete on the leaderboard

**Acceptance criteria:**

- [ ] Registration form validates username (3–50 chars), email format, password (min 8 chars)
- [ ] Duplicate username or email returns clear error
- [ ] Password stored as BCrypt hash (never plaintext)
- [ ] Successful registration redirects to login
- [ ] API: `POST /api/auth/register` returns 201

---

### US-1.2 Login (P0)

**As a** registered user  
**I want to** log in with my credentials  
**So that** I can access protected features

**Acceptance criteria:**

- [ ] Valid credentials return JWT token
- [ ] Invalid credentials return 401 with generic message (no user enumeration)
- [ ] Token stored in localStorage and attached to API requests
- [ ] Session persists across browser refresh until logout or expiry

---

### US-1.3 Logout (P0)

**As a** logged-in user  
**I want to** log out  
**So that** others cannot use my session on a shared device

**Acceptance criteria:**

- [ ] Logout clears token from storage
- [ ] User redirected to landing or login page
- [ ] Protected routes inaccessible after logout

---

### US-1.4 Protected routes (P0)

**As a** developer  
**I want** unauthenticated users blocked from app pages  
**So that** walk data remains private

**Acceptance criteria:**

- [ ] `/dashboard`, `/walk`, `/walks`, `/leaderboard`, `/profile` require JWT
- [ ] Missing token redirects to `/login`
- [ ] API returns 401 for missing/invalid JWT

---

## Epic 2: GPS walk tracking

### US-2.1 Start walk (P0)

**As a** walker  
**I want to** start a walk session  
**So that** the app begins recording my route

**Acceptance criteria:**

- [ ] "Start Walk" button on tracking page creates ACTIVE walk via API
- [ ] Browser requests geolocation permission if not granted
- [ ] Clear message if permission denied
- [ ] Only one active walk per user (409 if second start attempted)

---

### US-2.2 Record GPS points (P0)

**As a** walker  
**I want** my location recorded periodically during a walk  
**So that** my route is accurate

**Acceptance criteria:**

- [ ] Points collected every ~5 seconds while walk active
- [ ] Each point sent: lat, lng, timestamp, sequenceNumber
- [ ] Points stored with PostGIS `geom` POINT (EPSG:4326) — *Survey_Map pattern*
- [ ] Live polyline updates on map as points arrive
- [ ] Minimum movement filter optional (skip if < 5 m from last point)

---

### US-2.3 End walk (P0)

**As a** walker  
**I want to** stop my walk session  
**So that** my route is saved and stats computed

**Acceptance criteria:**

- [ ] "Stop Walk" ends session via API
- [ ] Server builds LINESTRING from points using `fn_build_walk_path`
- [ ] Distance computed server-side (`ST_Length` on geography) — not client Haversine
- [ ] Walk status becomes COMPLETED
- [ ] User navigated to walk detail page
- [ ] Walk rejected if fewer than 2 points

---

### US-2.4 Live walk stats (P1)

**As a** walker  
**I want to** see elapsed time and estimated distance during a walk  
**So that** I stay motivated

**Acceptance criteria:**

- [ ] Timer shows elapsed duration
- [ ] Distance shows client Haversine estimate labeled as approximate
- [ ] Final distance on detail page matches server value

---

## Epic 3: Route visualization

### US-3.1 View walk on map (P0)

**As a** user  
**I want to** see my completed walk on an OpenStreetMap  
**So that** I can review where I went

**Acceptance criteria:**

- [ ] Walk detail page shows Leaflet map with OSM tiles
- [ ] Route displayed as blue polyline
- [ ] Map zooms to fit route bounds
- [ ] GeoJSON path converted correctly [lng,lat] → [lat,lng]

---

### US-3.2 Walk statistics display (P0)

**As a** user  
**I want to** see distance, duration, and date for each walk  
**So that** I understand my activity

**Acceptance criteria:**

- [ ] Distance formatted (e.g., "3.2 km")
- [ ] Duration formatted (e.g., "45 min")
- [ ] Start date/time displayed in local timezone

---

## Epic 4: Dashboard and history

### US-4.1 Personal dashboard (P0)

**As a** user  
**I want a** dashboard with my overall stats  
**So that** I see my walking progress at a glance

**Acceptance criteria:**

- [ ] Shows total distance, total time, walk count
- [ ] Shows 5 most recent walks with links to detail
- [ ] Stats match sum of completed walks in database

---

### US-4.2 Walk history (P0)

**As a** user  
**I want to** browse all my past walks  
**So that** I can revisit any route

**Acceptance criteria:**

- [ ] Paginated list (20 per page)
- [ ] Sorted by date descending
- [ ] Each row links to walk detail
- [ ] Empty state when no walks

---

### US-4.3 Profile page (P1)

**As a** user  
**I want a** profile page with my stats  
**So that** I can share my progress

**Acceptance criteria:**

- [ ] Username and member-since date
- [ ] Same aggregate stats as dashboard

---

## Epic 5: Leaderboard

### US-5.1 Distance leaderboard (P0)

**As a** competitive walker  
**I want to** see how I rank against others by total distance  
**So that** I stay motivated to walk more

**Acceptance criteria:**

- [ ] Ranked list: rank, username, total distance, walk count
- [ ] Paginated (50 per page)
- [ ] Current user's rank shown even if not on current page
- [ ] Only COMPLETED walks count toward total

---

## Epic 6: Territory system (Phase 2)

### US-6.1 Closed-loop detection (P2)

**As a** walker  
**I want** the system to detect when I complete a loop  
**So that** I can claim territory

**Acceptance criteria:**

- [ ] On walk end, `fn_detect_closed_loop` runs
- [ ] Start/end within 25 m and perimeter ≥ 100 m
- [ ] Minimum 3 points for polygon

*Pattern: Survey_Map `ensureClosedPolygon` + server `fn_get_polygon_area`*

---

### US-6.2 Territory creation (P2)

**As a** walker  
**I want** my closed loop to become owned territory  
**So that** I control that area on the map

**Acceptance criteria:**

- [ ] `fn_create_territory_polygon` builds POLYGON from walk points
- [ ] `area_sq_meters` stored via `ST_Area(geography)`
- [ ] Territory linked to user and walk
- [ ] Notification/modal on walk end when territory created

---

### US-6.3 Territory map view (P2)

**As a** user  
**I want to** see territories on the map  
**So that** I understand the game world

**Acceptance criteria:**

- [ ] Territories rendered as filled polygons
- [ ] Tooltip: owner username, area
- [ ] Viewport query by bounding box

---

### US-6.4 Area leaderboard (P2)

**As a** competitive walker  
**I want** a leaderboard by total territory area  
**So that** loop walks have strategic value

**Acceptance criteria:**

- [ ] Rank users by sum of `area_sq_meters`
- [ ] Separate tab on leaderboard page

---

## Epic 7: Non-functional

### US-7.1 API performance (P0)

**Acceptance criteria:**

- [ ] List/history endpoints respond < 300 ms p95 with 10k walks in DB (indexed)
- [ ] Point insert < 100 ms p95

---

### US-7.2 Input validation (P0)

**Acceptance criteria:**

- [ ] All API inputs validated with Bean Validation
- [ ] SQL injection prevented (parameterized queries only)
- [ ] Users cannot access other users' walks (403)

---

## Definition of Done (all P0 stories)

- [ ] Code implemented per Backend-Spec / Frontend-Spec
- [ ] Unit or integration test for happy path
- [ ] API matches API-Spec.md
- [ ] No critical linter/security issues
- [ ] Manually verified in browser with GPS or mocked coordinates

---

## Test scenarios (GPS mocking for CI/dev)

| Scenario | Points | Expected |
|----------|--------|----------|
| Short walk | 10 points along line | distance > 0, path LINESTRING |
| Stationary | 5 identical points | distance ≈ 0 or rejected |
| Square loop 100m | 4 corners + close | Phase 2: territory ~10000 sq m |
| Open route | Start/end far apart | No territory |

